# {{ project_name }} (Raystack starter)

This scaffold behaves like a bare FastAPI app: in-memory demo data, no ORM required. Replace the sample routes when building your API.

## Run locally
- Create a virtualenv (optional) and install deps: `pip install "raystack" uvicorn`
- Start dev server: `python manage.py runserver --reload`
- Open http://127.0.0.1:8000

## Default routes
- `GET /` – welcome payload with a pointer back to this README
- `GET /api` – health check
- `GET /api/items` – list demo items (in-memory)
- `GET /api/items/{item_id}` – fetch one (404 when missing)
- `POST /api/items` – create (`{"name": "...", "description": "..."}`)
Data lives in memory and resets on restart.

## Add persistence later
Uncomment the example model in `app/models.py` and configure `DATABASES` in `config/settings.py` when you're ready to use the Raystack ORM.

